We faced an issue of passing the flag `compiler_options.po.experimental_simplifier` throughout the whole codebase to make the compiler decide whether to execute a piece of code based on that passed `--experimental-simplifer` flag.
So we decided to set a static global flag in `asr_utils.h` called `use_experimental_simplifier` to make us able to access that state of the  `compiler_options.po.experimental_simplifier`.

_In file `asr_utils.h` (lines 51- 55)_
```cpp
namespace LCompilers  {
    namespace ASRUtils  {
    static bool use_experimental_simplifier = false;
```
_in file `lfortran.cpp`(lines 2265 - 2266)_

```cpp
    CLI11_PARSE(app, argc, argv);
    LCompilers::ASRUtils::use_experimental_simplifier = compiler_options.po.experimental_simplifier;
```

Using a global variable to pass the message of critical information like `experimental-simplifier` flag isn't the best practice, so we need to find more secure way to do that.


